# Implementation Plan - Optimize ASTReadFileTool (Phase 2: Lazy & Config-Driven)

## Goal Description
Refactor [ASTReadFileTool](file:///Users/caishanghong/Shopify/cli-tool/llxprt-code-2/packages/core/src/tools/ast-edit.ts#1619-1700) to adopt a "Lazy > Eager" and "Working Set > Full Workspace" architecture. This solves the performance/memory CLI crash issues by:
1.  Disabling full workspace indexing by default (but preserving code behind a flag).
2.  Implementing on-demand, strictly limited `findInFiles` queries for context.
3.  Adding robust configuration and performance monitoring.

## User Review Required
> [!NOTE]
> **Philosophy**: We are shifting from "Index Everything" to "Query On Demand".
> **Backward Compatibility**: The old [buildSymbolIndex](file:///Users/caishanghong/Shopify/cli-tool/llxprt-code-2/packages/core/src/tools/ast-edit.ts#671-722) logic is preserved but marked `@deprecated` and disabled by default via `ASTConfig.ENABLE_SYMBOL_INDEXING = false`.

